The paper discusses the use of altmetrics data for societal impact measurements in scientometrics, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves analyzing mentions of scientific papers in policy-related documents, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the use of Web of Science (WoS) data suggests a focus on cryptography (cs.CR) as well.
